@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Our Story";
}

<section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Yes, We Used AI to Build This.</h1>
        <p class="lead">Transparency is our entire mission. So let&rsquo;s start with ourselves.</p>
    </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="manifesto-text">

            <p>Let&rsquo;s address the elephant in the room. You&rsquo;re visiting a website that certifies human-made
                work &mdash; and this website was built with the help of AI tools. The branding was brainstormed with an
                AI assistant. The manifesto was drafted with AI collaboration. The code was written with AI-powered tools.</p>

            <p class="pull-quote">We&rsquo;re transparent about that because transparency is our entire mission.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">We certify others &mdash; not ourselves.</h2>

            <p>CraftPledge certifies other people&rsquo;s work, not its own. Think of it like a food safety inspector
                &mdash; they don&rsquo;t have to be edible. An environmental auditor doesn&rsquo;t have to be a tree.
                What matters is that the certification process is rigorous, honest, and trustworthy.</p>

            <p>Our job is to build the most reliable, transparent system possible for verifying human-made work. How we
                build that system is a separate question from what the system certifies.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">Honest about the journey.</h2>

            <p>The founders used AI as a tool during the exploration phase &mdash; and they&rsquo;re honest about it.
                AI helped brainstorm ideas, draft content, and accelerate development. A human made every decision,
                wrote every final word, and takes full responsibility for the result.</p>

            <p>That&rsquo;s exactly what our <strong>Craft Assisted</strong> tier represents: AI as a tool, with a
                human at the helm.</p>

            <p class="pull-quote">This transparency is exactly what CraftPledge stands for.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">Building toward our own standard.</h2>

            <p>As the organisation matures, the goal is to move toward <strong>Craft Verified</strong> for our own
                outputs. We want our documentation, our marketing, our code, and our processes to be demonstrably
                human-made.</p>

            <p>But we&rsquo;re not going to pretend we&rsquo;re there yet. We&rsquo;re a startup. We used the tools
                available to us to get started. And we&rsquo;re telling you about it because that&rsquo;s the whole
                point.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <h2 class="manifesto-heading">The irony is the point.</h2>

            <p class="pull-quote">The fact that you can&rsquo;t tell if this manifesto was written by a human or an AI
                is exactly the problem we exist to solve.</p>

            <p>That uncertainty &mdash; that nagging question of &ldquo;was this real?&rdquo; &mdash; is precisely why
                CraftPledge needs to exist. In a world where the line between human and machine output is increasingly
                invisible, someone needs to make it visible again.</p>

            <p>That someone is us.</p>

            <hr class="section-divider my-5" />

            <p style="font-size:1.4rem;text-align:center;font-style:italic;color:var(--cp-terracotta);">
                We started this journey with AI. We&rsquo;re building toward a future where that choice is transparent.
                That&rsquo;s the point.
            </p>

        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- The Conversation -->
<section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:700px;">
        <div class="text-center mb-5">
            <h2>How it actually happened</h2>
            <hr class="section-divider" />
            <p class="text-warm-gray">
                Below is a recreation of the real conversation that started CraftPledge.
                A human with an idea, talking to an AI. It felt wrong not to show you.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="chat-conversation">

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>I&rsquo;ve been <span class="typo">thiking</span>. With AI everywhere now, people are conflicted. Should AI replace the artist? The crafter? I think there&rsquo;ll be a market for certifying things as &ldquo;not made by AI&rdquo; &mdash; like Fairtrade, but for human work. Do you think this is possible?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>Yes, absolutely. The pattern already exists &mdash; Fairtrade, Organic, Non-GMO. An &ldquo;AI-Free&rdquo; or &ldquo;Human-Made&rdquo; certification is a natural next step. The challenges will be verification and defining what counts as AI. But consumer demand for authenticity is real.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Give me name suggestions. Something that works as a URL.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>How about: craftpledge.org &mdash; &ldquo;Craft&rdquo; implies human skill, &ldquo;Pledge&rdquo; implies commitment and accountability. It&rsquo;s warm, brandable, and works for any industry.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>craftpledge.org is available. Write me a manifesto.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p><em>&ldquo;We believe in the human behind the work. Behind every great piece of work, there is a person&hellip;&rdquo;</em></p>
                <p style="font-size:0.85rem;opacity:0.7;">[Writes a 2,000-word manifesto about human craftsmanship in approximately 4 seconds]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Wait. How do we address the fact that we&rsquo;re using AI to create a brand about not using AI? The irony. I can&rsquo;t tell if this is something real or <span class="typo">sattire</span>.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>That&rsquo;s genuinely the most interesting tension in the whole idea. The best satire comes from a real truth. You could launch it as satire, let it become real, or keep the tension. My suggestion: build it, put it in front of people, and see if they laugh or say &ldquo;where do I sign up?&rdquo;</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>OK, build me a website. With .NET Aspire. Terraform for <span class="typo">infrastucture</span>. Bootstrap for styling. Make it look professional.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>Done. I&rsquo;ve created the solution, written the Terraform, built the CI/CD pipelines, and created seven pages of content about why human-made work matters. Build succeeds with zero warnings.</p>
                <p style="font-size:0.85rem;opacity:0.7;">[Creates an entire brand, infrastructure, and website for a human-craft certification &mdash; using AI]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Is there enough irony in the content?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>No. Let me add some more self-aware humour throughout the site.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Actually &mdash; wouldn&rsquo;t it be funny to just show this <span class="typo">converastion</span> on the website?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>You want me to write a recreation of the conversation where you asked an AI to build a human-craft certification brand, including the part where you asked if the irony was sufficient, and then asked me to put the conversation itself on the website?</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Yes.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-ai">
                <div class="chat-label">AI</div>
                <p>This is either the most honest thing on the internet or performance art. I genuinely can&rsquo;t tell.</p>
                <p style="font-size:0.85rem;opacity:0.7;">[Adds the conversation to the website]</p>
            </div>

            <div class="chat-bubble chat-human">
                <div class="chat-label">Human</div>
                <p>Both. That&rsquo;s the point.</p>
            </div>

        </div>

        <div class="text-center mt-5">
            <p class="text-warm-gray" style="font-style:italic;font-size:0.9rem;">
                This conversation is a dramatisation of real events. The actual conversation was longer,
                messier, and involved more tangents. But the essence is true. Every word on this website
                was shaped by a collaboration between a human and an AI &mdash; and now you know.
            </p>
        </div>

    </div>
</section>

<section class="cta-section">
    <div class="container">
        <h2>Honesty starts here</h2>
        <p>Read our manifesto to understand the values that drive everything we do.</p>
        <a asp-controller="Home" asp-action="Manifesto" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Read the Manifesto</a>
    </div>
</section>
